## Summary of Key Findings

*   **Enrollment:** Net Enrollment Ratio (NER) for age 6-14 is 98.5%.
*   **Learning Outcomes:**
    *   Std III: 10.5% can read Std II level text.
    *   Std V: 46.6% can read Std II level text.
    *   Std VIII: 83.5% can read Std II level text.
    *   Std III: 37.0% can do subtraction.
    *   Std V: 28.1% can do division.
    *   Std VIII: 76.7% can do division.
*   **Infrastructure:** Most schools have electricity and drinking water, but functional toilets and libraries remain a challenge in government schools.
*   **Teacher Quality:** Teacher attendance is high, but minimum qualifications vary.

## Methodology

ASER surveys are conducted annually in rural India. The survey covers all children aged 3-16 years in sampled villages. The sample is designed to be representative of the rural population. Data collection involves household visits and school visits. Learning assessments are conducted in the household. School infrastructure and teacher information are collected during school visits.

## Acknowledgements

ASER is a citizen-led initiative supported by a wide network of volunteers and partners. We thank all the families and schools who participated in the survey.

